 Mexico’s players celebrate at the end of the Russia 2018 World Cup Group F football match between South Korea and Mexico at the Rostov Arena in Rostov-On-Don on June 23, 2018. Mexico won 2-1.  / AFP PHOTO / JOE KLAMAR  An early penalty from Carlos Vela put Mexico ahead, and Javier Hernandez’s second-half goal secured the Central Americans’ second straight victory after stunning reigning champions Germany in their opening game, despite a late consolation from Son Heung-min. If Germany fail to beat Sweden later on Saturday, Mexico would go through and South Korea will be eliminated.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .